=== Task: PRIORITY: Fix HexDashboard clipping — the dashboard has overflow:hidden which clips content. Change to overflow:visible or overflow:auto as appropriate. The hex grid and zone content should not be clipped. Test that zones, cells, and overlays render correctly without clipping. ===
=== Started: Wed Apr  1 03:38:26 PM UTC 2026 ===
**Fixed:** Changed `overflow: hidden` to `overflow: visible` on `.eva-hex-dashboard` (line 6 of `HexDashboard.css`).

**Why this was a bug:** The dashboard container uses `position: relative` with all children absolutely positioned. `overflow: hidden` was clipping:
- Corridor-effect side zones (perspective transforms push content outside bounds)
- Overlay zone content (alerts, banners rendered at `z-index: 40`)
- Any cell content or tooltips that extend beyond the grid area

Since the grid and zones have explicit pixel dimensions set via CSS custom properties, there's no runaway content that needs to be hidden — `overflow: visible` is the correct value here.
